<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
The Phial of Galadriel on my <a class="external" href="./angband.oook.cz/ladder-show.php?id=3301"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">current character</a> does not seem to recharge.  I activated it once, but since then it has remained as (charging). I've uploaded the savefile to my webspace <a class="external" href=".www.cs.indiana.edu/~apvargo/Vargo_II"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">here</a>. I'm not sure if this is particular to 2.3 or not.  I don't remember ever seeing this behavior in previous versions. <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Try to use a newer version. This bug was introduced on 10/06/2004 with a bugfix, but was corrected a few days later (13/06/2004).  
<pre>10/06/2004
[B]- dungeon.c: Light should consume fuel at a rate of 1 / turn -- masmarangio
</pre>See also this <a class="external" href=".www.t-o-m-e.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4898"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">bug report</a> in the forum. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ElVargo">ElVargo</a>: Ah, thanks. <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
To anyone reading this, just remember that wearable things recharge when you wear them(whether that is intended or a bug is a mistery, but it's OK with me). 
</p>
